milestones.description: The day I felt I spiritually 'spawned' in 2nd grade at the age of 8, marking a significant awakening for me.

milestones.title: First Memory
milestones.description: A memory of walking around the neighborhood in my parents' first house in Ruidoso, New Mexico, with my mom. We would explore the area and walk down a giant hill.
milestones.significance: This memory makes me feel happy, and it also brings up feelings of missing my mom.

milestones.title: First Memory
milestones.description: A cherished moment with your mom in your first house in Ruidoso. You rode your scooter around the neighborhood, and you both walked down a giant hill back to your home.
milestones.significance: This memory reflects the joy of childhood and the bond with your mother.

milestones.title: Move to Euless, Texas
milestones.description: At the age of 5, you moved to Euless, Texas, marking a significant change in your life.
milestones.significance: This move represents a significant transition in your early life.

milestones.title: Starting Kindergarten
milestones.description: After moving to Euless, you began your kindergarten journey, entering formal education for the first time.
milestones.significance: Beginning school marked an exciting new chapter in your life.

milestones.title: Move to Bedford, Texas
milestones.description: After a year in Euless, you moved to Bedford, Texas, marking another significant transition.
milestones.significance: This move represented another change in your early life.

milestones.title: Met Best Friend Cody
milestones.description: In 1st grade, you made a new best friend named Cody, creating a meaningful connection during your childhood.
milestones.significance: This friendship was significant as it shaped your early social experiences.

milestones.title: Move to Hurst, Texas
milestones.description: After living in Bedford for five years, you moved to Hurst, Texas, continuing your journey.
milestones.significance: This move represents another chapter in your life.

milestones.title: Finishing Elementary School
milestones.description: Completed your elementary education in Hurst, Texas, marking the end of one phase of your education.
milestones.significance: This milestone reflects a foundational stage in your education.

milestones.title: Attending Bedford Junior High
milestones.description: Attended Bedford Junior High from 7th to 9th grade, experiencing the transition to middle school.
milestones.significance: This period marked the transition into adolescence and shaped your social experiences.

milestones.title: Graduating from L.D. Bell High School
milestones.description: Graduated from L.D. Bell High School after completing 10th to 12th grades.
milestones.significance: This achievement represents a significant academic milestone.

milestones.title: Moving to Texas Tech University
milestones.description: Transitioned to Texas Tech University to study computer science for five years, marking the first time living alone away from your parents.
milestones.significance: This move represents significant independence and a crucial step in your academic career.

milestones.title: Graduating from Texas Tech University
milestones.description: Completed your degree in computer science after five years of study.
milestones.significance: This achievement marks the culmination of your hard work and dedication.

milestones.title: Moving to Austin, Texas
milestones.description: After graduating in May 2019, you moved to Austin, Texas, embarking on a new chapter in your life.
milestones.significance: This move represents a step towards independence and new opportunities.

milestones.title: Starting My First Job
milestones.description: Began your career as a software engineer at General Motors on June 4th, 2019, marking the start of your professional journey.
milestones.significance: This milestone signifies the transition from education to a professional career.

milestones.title: Stopped Playing Soccer
milestones.description: After graduating high school in 2014, you decided to stop playing soccer, concluding a significant chapter in your athletic life. This decision had an impact on you as it meant no longer being part of a team sport, with your last team being in Hurst, Texas.
milestones.significance: This decision reflects a transition in your interests or priorities as you moved into adulthood.
